.TH "crypto_engine_alloc_init_and_set" 9 "crypto_engine_alloc_init_and_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
crypto_engine_alloc_init_and_set \- allocate crypto hardware engine structure and initialize it by setting the maximum number of entries in the software crypto-engine queue.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct crypto_engine *" crypto_engine_alloc_init_and_set
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "bool retry_support "  ","
.BI "int (*cbk_do_batch)(struct crypto_engine *engine) "  ","
.BI "bool rt "  ","
.BI "int qlen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device attached with one hardware engine
.IP "retry_support" 12
whether hardware has support for retry mechanism
.IP "cbk_do_batch" 12
pointer to a callback function to be invoked when executing
a batch of requests.
This has the form:
callback(struct crypto_engine *engine)
where:
.IP "rt" 12
whether this queue is set to run as a realtime task
.IP "qlen" 12
maximum size of the crypto-engine queue
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This must be called from context that can sleep.
.SH "RETURN"
the crypto engine structure on success, else NULL.
